@startuml
title Research Consent Lifecycle — State Diagram

state "GRANTED\n(active)" as GRANTED
state "REVOKED\n(terminal)" as REVOKED

[*] --> GRANTED : grantConsent(\n  patientId,\n  researchModuleId,\n  patientJourneyId,\n  grantedByUserId\n)\ngrantedAt = now()

GRANTED --> REVOKED : revokeConsent(\n  consentId,\n  revokedByUserId\n)\nrevokedAt = now()

REVOKED --> [*]

note right of GRANTED
  Idempotency:
  If an active Consent already exists
  for the same (patientId, researchModuleId,
  patientJourneyId), grantConsent returns
  the existing record without creating
  a duplicate.
end note

note right of REVOKED
  The record is NEVER deleted.
  revokedAt and revokedByUserId
  are set for audit purposes.
  hasActiveConsent() returns false.

  A new call to grantConsent
  after revocation creates a
  fresh Consent record.
  Both the revoked and the new
  record are preserved in
  AppState.researchConsents.
end note

note bottom
  Service: src/api/service/researchConsents.ts
  Storage: AppState.researchConsents[]
  UI: src/components/journey/ConsentDialog.tsx
end note

@enduml
